### Enums in Java

An enum (enumeration) is a special class that represents a fixed set of constants.

---

### Declaring an Enum

```java
enum Day {
    MONDAY, TUESDAY, WEDNESDAY, THURSDAY, FRIDAY, SATURDAY, SUNDAY
}
```

---

### Using Enums

```java
Day today = Day.MONDAY;

switch (today) {
    case MONDAY:
        System.out.println("Start of work week");
        break;
    case FRIDAY:
        System.out.println("TGIF!");
        break;
}
```

---

### Enum with Fields and Methods

```java
enum Planet {
    MERCURY(3.303e23, 2.4397e6),
    EARTH(5.976e24, 6.37814e6),
    JUPITER(1.9e27, 7.1492e7);

    private final double mass;
    private final double radius;

    Planet(double mass, double radius) {
        this.mass = mass;
        this.radius = radius;
    }

    public double getMass() { return mass; }
}
```

---

### Enum Methods

| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `values()` | Returns all enum constants |
| `valueOf(String)` | Returns enum constant by name |
| `ordinal()` | Returns position (0-based) |
| `name()` | Returns constant name as string |

---

### Enum with Abstract Methods

```java
enum Operation {
    ADD { int apply(int a, int b) { return a + b; } },
    SUBTRACT { int apply(int a, int b) { return a - b; } };
    abstract int apply(int a, int b);
}
```

> **Key Point:** Enums are implicitly `final` and extend `java.lang.Enum`. They can have constructors, fields, and methods. Enum constructors are always private.

codeExample:
enum Status {
    PENDING("Waiting for approval"),
    APPROVED("Application approved"),
    REJECTED("Application rejected");

    private final String description;

    Status(String description) {
        this.description = description;
    }

    public String getDescription() {
        return description;
    }

    public boolean isFinal() {
        return this == APPROVED || this == REJECTED;
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Status current = Status.PENDING;

        System.out.println("Current: " + current);
        System.out.println("Description: " + current.getDescription());
        System.out.println("Is final: " + current.isFinal());

        // Iterate all values
        for (Status s : Status.values()) {
            System.out.println(s.ordinal() + ": " + s.name() + 
                " - " + s.getDescription());
        }

        // Switch with enum
        switch (current) {
            case PENDING:
                System.out.println("Please wait...");
                break;
            case APPROVED:
                System.out.println("Approved!");
                break;
            case REJECTED:
                System.out.println("Rejected");
                break;
        }
    }
}
